position overview
the climate corporation is seeking bright creative scientific computing expert to join the fertility science team we leverage big data and cloud computing to tackle real-world problem in agriculture including crop nutrient and risk management we work with weather data environmental sensor soil measurement agricultural statistic geological survey satellite imagery and more we are looking for scientific engineer who are passionate about working with domain expert to design build and evaluate model to support farmers' decision on nutrient management
what you will do
design build and test new algorithm and model in a fast-paced iterative development environment
work closely with agronomist crop modeler statistician and data scientist to implement scientific algorithm in research and production environment
engage in model calibration and performance testing using multiple source of ground truth data
develop and apply numerical solution to fluid flow problem and other system of partial differential equation
work with engineer to implement model in a production environment
basic qualifications
phd or ms ma + 2 year of relevant experience in an engineering field with emphasis in scientific computing including applied mathematics chemical engineering civil environmental engineering agricultural engineering or physic
two year of experience writing code in a team environment industry or academic
deep understanding and fluency of at least one compiled language preferably java and one scripting language
experience with data processing and statistical analysis tool using r matlab python or similar
preferred qualifications
mastering best engineering practice and able to write well-structured maintainable performant and well-documented code with an emphasis on scientific code correct naming of variable fluency in unit experience translating scientific model into code
experience in agricultural ecosystem science including hydrology nutrient cycling soil science agronomy
experience working with large data set
